      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The first of the features now and ROYAL TORONADO (3) looks the one to beat off back-to-back wins. He bolted in to win the Pinjarra Cup last start by 2.6L and while he rises in weight, he boasts 3 wins from 5 starts at this track and trip. Pike rides from a good draw and it's hard to see anything turning the tables. FANCY RED (5) wasn't beaten far in the Bunbury Cup before dropping back to the mile last start where they were too zippy. Now back out in distance and she can take up the running under CJP who replaces the apprentice. Can get back to winning ways. OUTSPOKEN LAD (7) bolted in to win the Narrogin Cup a fortnight ago in good style. This is tougher, but he turned in a strong figure there and Brad Parnham now hops on board. Can be in the finish if he holds his form. TRIO (6) steps out in trip now and can improve. OLY'S CHOICE (2) is building nicely after a long layoff and won't be far away.",
